sub_title: Historical Research Student Comparative European Focus
summary:
The ability to analyse and learn quickly, the constructive and goal-orientated interaction in groups, and a great personal motivation to understand complex historical and contemporary processes constitute my core strengths. 

The participation in the honour’s programme of the Faculty of Arts and an Erasmus exchange to Oslo equipped me with experience in independent academic research and networking. Consequently, experiencing life in Germany, Ireland, the Netherlands, Norway and Slovenia provided me with an open and international mind-set. Additionally, my work as a European volunteer in a youth-centre enabled me to cooperate constructively in a team, while developing my own initiatives independently and taking up responsibilities in the daily activities with the youngsters. In my free time, I am engaged in several social and sportive associations.
